<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<TestCaseEntity>
   <description>As a CDAT user I want to change a forgotten password so I can access the system. 

Acceptance Criteria: 

RM-92.1: CDAT provides a Forgot Password option on the login page. 

RM-92.2: CDAT displays the following message when a user selects the Forgot Password option (The user is required to enter their user name): 

&quot;Enter your username and we will email you a password reset link.&quot; 

RM-92.3: CDAT sends a unique hashed URL to the user 's registered email . The user is directed to the Change Password screen after selecting the URL to initiate a password change. 

RM-92.4: CDAT requires the user to enter a new password that meets CMS Security requirements. 

RM-92.5: CDAT requires the user to re-enter their new password for confirmation. 

RM-92.6: 
 CDAT requires the user to select the Change Password option to complete the process. 

RM-92.7: 
CDAT displays the following message if password does not meet CMS requirements: 

&quot;The password entered does not meet CMS Security requirements.&quot; 

RM-92.8: CDAT directs the user back to the login page upon successful password reset. The user is required to enter their username and new password and go through the multifactor authentication before being allowed to log in.</description>
   <name>RM_92_Forgot Password</name>
